Edit:

You also need to add the `output` to the `JFrame`. You tried this by using

    frame.add(output);
    frame.add(panel);

but that won&#39;t work. The content pane of a `JFrame` by default has a `BorderLayout`, and calling `add` will add the component in the `BorderLayout#CENTER`. That area can only contain one component.

Now you have two options:

- Change the `LayoutManager`. [This][2] is a good overview of the standard available `LayoutManager`s.
- Keep the current `LayoutManager`, and add the two components to different areas, e.g.

        frame.add(output, BorderLayout.CENTER);
        frame.add(panel, BorderLayout.SOUTH);

  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/javax/swing/JTextArea.html#append-java.lang.String-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/layout/visual.html

